io.branch.referral

Class Branch.ReferralNetworkCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.branch.referral.Branch.ReferralNetworkCallback
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NetworkCallback
    Enclosing class:
    Branch

    public class Branch.ReferralNetworkCallback
extends java.lang.Object
implements NetworkCallback

    A class that implements NetworkCallback interface and provides the required state and response logic for the process of interacting with the Branch referral network service.

    The class takes a ServerResponse instance as a parameter, and determines action taken based primarily upon the states code returned by the Branch server response.

    Handled status codes are as follows:

    • 200 - OK
    • 409 - Duplicate link error.
    • 401 - 499 - Server-side error. API issue.

    Assuming then that an error has not occurred, and that code 200 is the status, the static values defined in the BranchRemoteInterface class are compared against the value of ServerResponse.getTag() method call to determine the action to take.

    Possible values are as follows:

    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_REGISTER_INSTALL
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_REGISTER_OPEN
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_REGISTER_CLOSE
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_COMPLETE_ACTION
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_GET_REFERRAL_COUNTS
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_GET_REWARDS
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_REDEEM_REWARDS
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_GET_REWARD_HISTORY
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_GET_CUSTOM_URL
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_IDENTIFY
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_LOGOUT
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_GET_REFERRAL_CODE
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_VALIDATE_REFERRAL_CODE
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_APPLY_REFERRAL_CODE
    • BranchRemoteInterface.REQ_TAG_SEND_APP_LIST
    See Also:
